## IndexParser

![screen-shot](Example/Screen Shot.png)


This project is part of [Tea Box](http://www.lisacintosh.com/tea-box/) application.

This is a Mardown-like formatting class to convert plain text to HTML (with Javascript for interactive elements).

I've created this application in febuary 2013 and I release the code source and resources on MIT Licence.

_Xcode 4.6+ and Mac OS X.6 required._

[Download Tea Box](http://lisacintosh.com/tea-box/)

[Lisacintosh.com](http://lisacintosh.com/), 2014


-----

The syntax is:

#### Headers:

`#Bigger Header Ever` will looks like:
#Bigger Header Ever

`##Nice and Big Header` will looks like:
##Nice and Big Header
<br>

`###Nice Header` will looks like:
#####Nice Header
<br>


#### Font Format:

`*bold is bold*` will looks like: **bold is bold**
<br><br>

`_something better in italic_` will looks like: _something better in italic_
<br><br>

`~~something to stroke through~~` will looks like: ~~something to stroke through~~

#### Web links:
`@lisacintosh.com` will looks like:

[lisacintosh.com](http://lisacintosh.com)

#### Checkboxes:
`- [ ] Must be done` will looks like:

<!-- Inline data, so 2010's! -->
<img width="16" height="16" title="" alt="" src="data:image/png;base64,"/> Must be done

`- [x] It's done!` will looks like:

<img width="16" height="16" title="" alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /> It's done!

#### Countdowns:
`{ 8/10 } Need to done 2 times more` will looks like:

<img width="38" height="48" src="data:image/png;base64," /> Need to done 2 times more

#### Step Links:
`Look this step: [Step name]` will looks like:
<pre>Look this step: <a href="#" style="color:#555;">Step name</a></pre>
